**List of the literature on Vegetation greening and FRP/fire intensity**

1. Tong, X., Brandt, M., Yue, Y. et al. Increased vegetation growth and carbon stock in China karst via ecological engineering. Nat Sustain 1, 44–50 (2018). https://doi.org/10.1038/s41893-017-0004-x
2. Piao, S., Wang, X., Park, T. et al. Characteristics, drivers and feedbacks of global greening. Nat Rev Earth Environ 1, 14–27 (2020). https://doi.org/10.1038/s43017-019-0001-x
3. Li, X., Wang, K., Huntingford, C. et al. Vegetation greenness in 2023. Nat Rev Earth Environ 5, 241–243 (2024). https://doi.org/10.1038/s43017-024-00543-z
4. Satellite-Observed Major Greening and Biomass Increase in South China Karst During Recent Decade: https://doi.org/10.1029/2018EF000890
5. Ground- and satellite-based evidence of the biophysical mechanisms behind the greening Sahel: https://doi.org/10.1111/gcb.12807
